Construction, Project and Program Management
Since 1998 Meridian Management, Inc. (Meridian) has been a leader in Alaska for providing professional project management services, and owner representation is our specialty. We approach projects with an attitude toward teamwork and collaboration, while still looking out for our clients’ best interests and mitigating their risk.
Meridian has a successful performance record for delivering capital projects for private and public entities, in both non-profit and for-profit sectors.  We do not limit our services to any one industry, or minimum project size.  Meridian has managed projects across the state, from Wrangell to Barrow to Dillingham.
Our services include management of capital projects through the entire project life-cycle from design and construction through commissioning and closeout. Depending on the need, we can also manage a specific portion of a project (e.g. solicitation, project controls, etc.). Meridian can also manage clients’ entire capital improvement programs consisting of multiple projects.
What Sets Us Apart?
Meridian is an employee-owned, Alaskan corporation and our staff takes pride in ownership of our work product, and this is reflected by repeat business and referrals from our clients. We work hard to keep our overhead low and maintain competitive rates, which allow our clients to stretch their limited resources.
Our clients appreciate our “hands-on” approach and the experience we bring. Our project managers emphasize communication and resolving issues at the lowest possible level. We stress the importance of on-site quality assurance and bring with us a tool box of experience, certifications and training. Meridian project managers don’t show up to jobsites with shiny new hard hats and boots, unless they just wore them out.






