"Bridging the gap between ideas and reality"


Founded in 1998, Meridian Management, LLC is a unique design firm specializing in innovative solutions for the telecom and wireless industries. The firm is the realization of a vision to bring together design expertise with an in-depth understanding of wireless development in order to provide state-of-the-art design solutions to our clients.
We offer a wealth of experience in all disciplines required to develop telecommunications, tower, wireless, small cell, joint pole, and DAS sites. We have pioneered innovative methods for the entire design process, enabling our clients to streamline municipal permitting and go on-air in a reduced timeframe. We invite you to learn more about who we are and how we can help you.



"These guys are the best. They're a pleasure to work with and they do great work."
John Neal
					Alcatel-Lucent
					Outside Plant Services








About Us


The Beginning


Meridian Management, LLC began as a specialized consulting firm providing high-end 3D, animation, and technical CAD services to the architectural community in the SF Bay Area. In 1997, the firm was contracted by Nextel to design a number of raw land telecom sites, due in large part to the extensive experience with zoning, site development, visualization, and planning work. With a background in site development, the firm began to specialize in telecom work and quickly became a leader in the field. In 1999, Rodney Barnes, a telecommunications professional with years of technical experience, joined the firm. The foundation of a strong architectural/telecommunications base was complete. This 'union' of talent is the strength of our service and the reason why we have enjoyed steady growth, success, and repeat business throughout the firm's history



"There isn't an A/E firm that I've come to rely on more than Meridian Management LLC. Their collective experience and knowledge are invaluable to us."
AAV Construction
					Manager
					T-Mobile USA


Our Approach


At Meridian Management, LLC, we are keenly aware of the rapidly changing telecom environment. Advanced networking systems including the development of 4G, LTE, DAS, and joint pole installations requires the design professional to adapt in ways like never before. We understand these challenges and are continually striving to develop faster, cheaper, and more efficient ways of designing wireless facilities. Among these services include specializing in turn-key solutions for joint pole facilities, sustainable LEED-based designs for raw land sites, streamlining the LTE equipment upgrade process, and pioneering a web-based site auditing process.
We also understand the competitive nature of the wireless industry and the scheduling and budget constraints inherent in this type of work. In response to these demands, Meridian Management, LLC employs a deliberate and controlled approach to the development of each project. On the premise that each project requires a blend of professional expertise, we employ a collaborative approach to a project's development from initial site visit through construction documentation. The firm's principals are actively involved on each project, thus assuring the highest level of service, availability, and responsiveness each site deserves.



Our Mission

We are firm believers in designing telecom facilities to seamlessly integrate into their existing setting. We also understand the need to conceal this equipment to the best of our abilities. We continuously promote an in-depth understanding of the site in an effort to develop design strategies that are efficient, practical, and compatible with both the environment, existing conditions, owner expectations, and the general public.
Our mission is simple:

To never be satisfied
To always strive to be better and more efficient
To achieve customer satisfaction and profitability
To be pioneers, to redefine boundaries, to take risks
To be the best!




Key Staff


Jan M. Goldfluss, President, brings to the company over 31 years of professional experience in site development, telecommunications facilities, landscape architecture, project management, computer applications, planning, and construction management. As company founder, Jan has been responsible for designing and managing over 1,500 telecommunications sites for clients throughout the US. As a central player in the firm's growth and development, Jan serves as Director of Design and Production, where he plans, manages, tracks, and provides quality control for all the firm's project work.  He also serves as the Director for New Business Development.  In this role, his high-level guidance impacts long range planning, marketing efforts, new products development, and all other aspects of client services. He is also active in the creation of the firm's innovative products and services including DAS systems and pole top sites.



Rodney Barnes, Vice President, has over 22 years in telecom and helps focus on the process and not merely the results. His extensive experience working with a wide range of telecommunications carriers and third-party vendors provided the technical foundation that contributed to the firm's growth and success. His involvement in telecommunications goes back to Nextel in 1994 where he was one of the first individuals to work in all three site development disciplines - leasing, zoning and construction. Clients continually tap into his vast knowledge of the entire build process to expedite approvals, constructability issues and cost savings. Rodney has developed a complete understanding of the implementation of ROW usage. He has extensive knowledge of JPA and GO95 requirements. Rodney serves as Vice President and Director of Client Relations and Operations.









Services


Telecom Design


The design of telecommunications sites involves a whole range of capabilities and experience. At Meridian Management LLC, we employ a comprehensive approach to the design of cell sites including a full range of engineering services, constructability analysis, site and landscape design, surveying, and visual simulation. Our strength is in our understanding of site constraints and exactly what is required to obtain building permits and allow bidding and construction to proceed. With this in mind, Meridian Management LLC's technical and architecture professionals design custom site solutions for a broad array of telecommunications facilities. From hillsides to rooftops, co-locatable poles to faux trees, steeples to architectural additions, and water tanks to billboards, the professionals at Meridian Management LLC will work with you to provide the most practical, cost-effective, and approvable design possible.














