DAS Systems


With the growing demand for broadband services, wireless carriers across the U.S. are finding that their existing networks sometimes are inadequate. They are turning to Distributed Antenna System (DAS) networks as an attractive option where macro cell sites cover too many users, zoning ordinances restrict locating antennas on towers or rooftops, or there is a need to offload macro-cellular traffic to alleviate data traffic congestion.
At Meridian Management LLC, we work with carriers in the planning, designing, and permitting of DAS networks to optimize network operations while minimizing the infrastructural footprint.
We offer our clients a cost-effective and efficient approach to the design of node and hub facilities, including:


Site Acquisition
Site Auditing
Lease Exhibits
Architectural Design
Structural Engineering
Electrical Engineering
Concealment Design








Site Auditing


Audits, both file and site, are an important part of the wireless industry today and for the foreseeable future. Audits are performed for a variety of reasons but generally for license applications, inventory requirements, and database creation and verification. 
Understanding the importance of site audits, the professionals at Meridian Management LLC in 2008 founded a subsidiary firm Audigent to offer state-of-the art web-based applications to complete audits more effectively and efficiently.
 





Advantages


Reduces time needed to complete and finalize audits Standardizes data collection 
Fully functional help menus and support call-in facilitates on-site accuracy
Completely customizable auditing templates
Web-based audit forms can be accessed from virtually anywhere
Intelligent database provides relevant information for technical, financial, and marketing purposes
Consistency of auditors trained in only one proven method of data gathering
Password protected to insure security




